I"b<p>Those who follow this link already know that  I have been working with my co-authors from XX Networks, David Chaum and Mario Yaksetig to develop a special trick for wallets. The idea is that in a major, and catastrophic, event when several wallets are hacked, there is still a possibility of the rightful user issues a proof ownership of the wallet. This is the inspiration for our work with</p>

<p>Events like that had already occurred therefore it seems highly desirable that wallets have such capability.</p>

<p>We are now working on the final version of the work and it will soon be made public!</p>

